        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "usp_Published_ActiveAccountsNotBilledReport",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " generates a report of active accounts that have not been billed for all months within a specified billing period range. It logs the report usage, retrieves the current billing period, and adjusts the end of the billing period if it exceeds the current period. The procedure then queries the database to find accounts that have been billed fewer times than the number of months in the specified range, indicating they have not been billed for every month."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
